#######
# DWM #
#######

### dwm execution (startup automatically) ###
1) install startx 
2) append `exec dwm` (remove backticks `) in ~/.xinitrc
3) append `exec startx dwm` (remove backticks `) in ~/.bash_profile
4) reboot

### backend portals configuration for dwm (recommended way) ###
1) create ~/.config/environment.d/ then touch 10-env-var.conf in it.
2) define all needed environment variable that you need (that dwm cannot find) like: XDG_CURRENT_DESKTOP, DISPLAY ..., as follows: 
	XDG_CURRENT_DESKTOP=dwm
	DISPLAY=:0
3) put the following in ~/.xinitrc (create if doesn't exist):
	#get any defined environment variables in ~/.config/environment.d/ and put them in the following commands:	
	systemctl --user import-environment XDG_CURRENT_DESKTOP DISPLAY	
	dbus-update-activation-environment --systemd XDG_CURRENT_DESKTOP=dwm DISPLAY=:0

### backend portals configuration for dwm (notrecommended way) ###
export environment variables dwm could not find in ~/.xinitrc

### dwm default theme to dark (dependency: breeze-gtk) ###
gsettings set org.gnome.desktop.interface gtk-theme 'Adwaita-Dark'
gsettings set org.gnome.desktop.interface icon-theme 'Adwaita-Dark'
# gsettings set org.gnome.desktop.interface cursor-theme 'Adwaita-Dark' or 'Future-cyan-cursors'
# gsettings set org.gnome.desktop.interface color-scheme 'prefer-dark'
gsettings set org.gtk.Settings.FileChooser startup-mode cwd #cwd = home

########
# WIFI #
########

connect to a hidden wifi:
nmcli connection reload
nmcli device wifi rescan ssid <ssid to scan> 
nmcli -a device wifi connect <ssid> hidden yes private yes 

###################
# Keyboard layout #
###################

localectl set-x11-keymap us,ara acer_laptop , grp:win_space_toggle (for win+space toggle)
localectl set-x11-keymap us,ara acer_laptop , grp:alt_shift_toggle (for alt+shift toggle)
OR:
setxkbmap -model acer_laptop -option grp:alt_shift_toggle us,ara (add in xinitrc or xprofile)

#####â„–###
# Audio #
#########

* remove wireplumber config to get youtube videos running
* fix mpd.service not starting for user mode by adding `ProtectKernelModules=no` in ~/.config/systemd/user/mpd.service 

#################
# Miscellaneous #
#################

* edit env variables via systemd: systemctl --user (import/show/set/unset)-environment {env variable...}
* add your user to wheel group & adding `wheel ALL=(ALL:ALL) ALL` to /etc/sudoers file 
* add your user to input, mpd and wheel groups for waybar-keyboard-state module
* install: webkit2gtk-4.(something) & gcr to avoid suckless surf compilation problems 

